  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2004-02-11",
    "date": "2004-04-14T21:22:00Z",
    "text": "Safeguarding Assets For Employees in Bankruptcy Act of 2004 - Amends Federal bankruptcy law to: (1) increase from $4,000 to $20,000 the dollar amount of specified unsecured claims related to employment benefits in the third and fourth priority tier; and (2) place in fifth order of priority the allowed unsecured claims of employees arising under the Worker Adjustment and Retraining Notification Act."
